article.description: — Jalen Thomas had 16 points as Georgia State got past Appalachian State 58-49 on Saturday.
article.headline: Thomas carries Georgia St. over Appalachian St. 58-49
article.linkText: Thomas carries Georgia St. over Appalachian St. 58-49
article.story: BOONE, N.C. -- — Jalen Thomas had 16 points as Georgia State got past Appalachian State 58-49 on Saturday. Kane Williams had 12 points for Georgia State (11-10, 5-5 Sun Belt Conference), which earned its fourth straight road victory. Justin Roberts added 11 points. Corey Allen had 10 points. Appalachian State scored 16 points in the first half, a season low for the team. Justin Forrest had 12 points for the Mountaineers (16-11, 10-4). Adrian Delph added 12 points and seven rebounds. Michael Almonacy had eight rebounds. The Panthers evened the season series against the Mountaineers. Appalachian State defeated Georgia State 61-60 on Jan. 20. ------ For more AP college basketball coverage: https://apnews.com/hub/college-basketball and http://twitter.com/AP--Top25 ------ This was generated by Automated Insights, http://www.automatedinsights.com/ap, using data from STATS LLC, https://www.stats.com
